 fail unless reachability metadata covers the reflective methods for BouncyCastle classes. I’m considering the need to add this metadata manually since there won't be a run agent available. It feels essential to get this right for successful execution.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_agGnqAuNNdvvwRIzNjDILenS|fc_05f0c74f02cd07fb0169f95055e4588190b6c2fab2f7b3176f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata/org.bouncycastle -maxdepth 4 -type f -name reachability-metadata.json -print | sort | head -30 && find metadata/org.bouncycastle -maxdepth 3 -type f -name index.json -print -exec sh -c 'echo ---$1; head -50 $1' _ {} \\;", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2307, "output": 1093, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31560, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777946696748, "responseId": "resp_05f0c74f02cd07fb0169f9504937848190b03e8ca33fee5c95"}}
