[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering library dependencies**\n\nI need to use bcpkix along with bcprov due to OpenSSL and PKCS packages. The bcpkix-jdk15on:1.70 version depends on both bcprov and bcutil. I wonder if there could be a newer split package causing duplicate issues if bcprov is optional, but likely not. There's also a potential issue with BouncyCastle Provider registration where it could fail if it already exists. \n\nI want to ensure Native Image support and that reflective methods have the necessary configuration, but I'm debating whether we should edit metadata manually. It seems I'll need to run tests for coverage in the workflow, though.\n\n**Examining test execution for Native Image**\n\nThe developer rules specify that Native Image tests should run by default, and any missing reachability metadata tests need to execute under Native Image as well. If I incorporate a test using BouncyCastlePrivateKeyFactory in the native context, it will likely fail unless reachability metadata covers the reflective methods for BouncyCastle classes. I’m considering the need to add this metadata manually since there won't be a run agent available. It feels essential to get this right for successful execution.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05f0c74f02cd07fb0169f95049c7ac8190bc429ce222c82687\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-VBVzT5ey2_fSkwvLXGgGCfmNSnjE2NlFsmjmBSiNkDUp3Eiu0cQGpNCIdqW8Tc7V8d2VX-igyKj-EhCD5CwjD3QzbTn6mym59VuEfoN9Cm-FGluQE4G8pjytgLl2BYF4BN2-8Q_esWmQTWVZAWj6Kn-Gpuui-_Q26kWoqbjtSAzvaDJheOalwOxigK5AVKwXju7A2558UffA8uNCvWqUG4W7UC042_kPqHS_PBapFv8LG0N-HIwj4s2o0Fzrr9ZJKAD4F7aeFzxdgy3un0bXva59ZrFtgfeCoSrMhjQCsKKfWurbnnDTCWGmrEHak4V6tYl-vCU4VBwDzP_Vu9VupoF-A3ThdJcvcP8HT0PPdxU6p6pRlx23tL2XH4df4t637XRKgOkleQwZeolmX9-ABvHMKMiftl1J9qqhCrwlO0zaXOSOZQUEFLkRS9An-n-a6cCgqlcvo6UgVs_zQx41f2LPUSTMW1jSgAc4n0lNUrTdKf7FV9sa6-GufQbK1UbFCmAMNi2oIzLGLqc6DjGuRQb-_g21AA_